<div class="post">
			
				<div class="post-inner">
				
				<div class="post-head">

					<h2 class="headline"><a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/2010/06/19/the-virtual-whirl-a-crisis-of-confidence/">The Virtual Whirl: A crisis of confidence</a> </h2>

					<p class="byline">by <a class="byline-author" href="/editor/tateru-nino">Tateru Nino</a> <a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/editor/tateru-nino/rss.xml"><img src="http://www.blogsmithmedia.com/massively.joystiq.com/media/writer_rss.gif" /></a> (6 months ago)</p>

<p class="post-cats"><a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/business-models/">Business models</a>, <a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/culture/">Culture</a>, <a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/mmo-industry/">MMO industry</a>, <a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/opinion/">Opinion</a>, <a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/second-life/">Second Life</a>, <a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/virtual-worlds/">Virtual worlds</a>, <a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/the-virtual-whirl/">The Virtual Whirl</a></p>
					
					<div class="comment-count"><a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/2010/06/19/the-virtual-whirl-a-crisis-of-confidence/#comments">25</a><span class="tail"></span></div>
					
				</div>
				
				<div class="post-body">

				
					<p><a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/category/the-virtual-whirl/"><img hspace="4" vspace="4" border="1" alt="" style="display: block; float: none; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/massively.joystiq.com/media/2010/01/vwhirl4-580.jpg" /></a></p>
<p>Most things in the world operate on faith. Governments, currencies, intellectual property, human rights and brands all require certain minimum levels of belief and confidence in order to function.</p>
<p>When it comes to virtual environments, as I've maintained in the past, faith is critical.</p>
                                        <p class="continue-reading"><a href="http://massively.joystiq.com/2010/06/19/the-virtual-whirl-a-crisis-of-confidence/">Continue Reading</a></p>
					
					

					 
				</div>

				
				<div class="post-meta">
				
					<ul class="sources">
						
                                                
                                                
                                                
					</ul>

					
